<P>
   CRITICS-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Critic's Notebook: When composers
ask musicians to do the impossible. By Bernard Holland.
</P>
<P>
   MONET-EXHIBIT (Paris) _ Arts Abroad: Paris has another great
Monet exhibit. By Alan Riding.
</P>
<P>
   WALLACE-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Brief Interviews With Hideous
Men,'' by David Foster Wallace. By Michiko Kakutani.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; STYLE (Moved in ``l'' category) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DUTCH-DESIGNERS (New York) _ Why are all these fanatically cool
people pouring into Visionaire, the fashion publisher and art
gallery in SoHo, to check out the latest haute couture creations by
a couple of Dutch designers named Viktor Horsting and Rolf Snoeren?
By Cathy Horyn.
</P>
