<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ TEEPEN-COLUMN _ At last, an explanation for the
low-level emotional miasma that I've dragged along all these years
like swamp fog _ uncomplaining, even saint-like if I do say so
myself, in my silent martyrdom, bearing my own angst with debonair
grit. It's all GI Joe's fault. (Tom Teepen is national
correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED FRIDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ CASABLANCA, Morocco -- The 1942 classic
``Casablanca'' is a nostalgic, romantic fantasy that has no basis
in fact. But we all want to believe it is real. If you are one of
those, today's Casablanca could be disillusioning. (Kleinberg, Cox
News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN02 _ ``Tacky'' is a pejorative southern word noted
for its flexibility of meaning. ``Tacky'' can describe anything
from the paint on the front porch floor to your son's new
girlfriend's tattoo. And no matter how it's used, it's always a
ladylike thing to say. (Schuett, Cox News Service). MOVED SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORIAL-MILOSEVIC _ The indictment last week of Yugoslavian
President Slobodan Milosevic by the International War Crimes
Tribunal is an interesting turn in the ongoing Balkan saga.
However, the tribunal's efforts in capturing indicted war criminals
and bringing them to trial has been nothing short of futile. In
fact, its failure has undermined confidence in the tribunal itself
_ thus making it little more than a sham body with few means of
enforcing its legal activities. (Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-LAMB-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Emergency doctors and
paramedics have lost lawsuits in Ohio both for reviving someone who
didn't want to be revived and for not reviving someone whose family
wanted a heroic effort, says Dr. David Romano, who served with
Keseg on the committee that drafted the new law's rules. The
solution is House Bill 354, called ``DNR Comfort Care'' for ``do
not resuscitate.'' It means people who are terminally ill or have
end-stage organ disease can, with their physician's authorization,
receive assurance of dying as peacefully as possible. (Lamb, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
