traffic along faster has led to problems in the suburbs: streets
aren't safe and people are getting hurt; so a new wave of street
design is hitting the area as cities put obstacles in the path of
traffic to slow it down and make roads safer for bicyclists and
pedestrians. Robert Cronkleton.
