<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (London) _ Thank goodness there'll always be an
England. Someone has to keep the rest of us amused. Last week a
furor erupted in Parliament over welfare reform, and Prime Minister
Tony Blair edged out further on a shaky limb to press NATO's war
against Yugoslavia. But the only thing that gripped the public was
a photo in the Sun of Prince Edward's fiancee, Sophie Rhys-Jones,
with a breast bared and the giant press dust-up it produced. By
MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
