<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A LETTER TO CLEVELAND, AND A ERNIE FORD FAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service Clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: My sister came across a letter from President Grover
Cleveland that was written personally to her grandfather. It is
still in the original envelope and dated. What is it worth?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.S., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The value of the item depends on two things: what he wrote
and whether he was president at the time.
</P>
<P>
   Bill Panagopulus, president of Alexander Autographs in
Greenwich, Conn., said Cleveland autographs and letters are
generally worth about $150 to $400. Prices for presidential letters
increase greatly if they have historical value.
</P>
<P>
   He lists Cleveland with Benjamin Harrison and Herbert Hoover as
presidents who don't ``stir any fire in the soul'' with most
collectors. ``It's really how sexy the president is,'' he said. The
least-collected chief executive, according to Panagopulus, is
Millard Fillmore.
</P>
<P>
   To contact Alexander Autographs, call (203) 622-8444 or visit
the www.alexautographs.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find Tennessee Ernie Ford's gospel music?
</P>
<P>
   _ S.O.L., Kingsport, Tenn.
</P>
<P>
   A: Music By Mail and other retailers sell a two-CD collection of
Ford's gospel music, ``Amazing Grace: 40 Treasured Hymns,''
released in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   To order from Music By Mail, call (800) 678-8863 or visit
www.websterrecords.com.
</P>
<P>
   Ford, who died in 1991 at age 72, was raised in Bristol, Tenn.,
and worked there as a disc jockey while studing music. Capitol
Records signed Ford to his first recording contract in 1948, and he
was inducted into the Country Music Hall of Fame in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I'd like to write my first fan letter at age 70. Where can I
write to Neil Diamond?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.M., Bridgeport, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Letters should be sent in care of the official fan club,
Friends of Neil Diamond, Box 3357, Hollywood, CA 90028. Or send an
e-mail by visiting the Web site www.diamondville.com.
</P>
<P>
   His tour schedule is available on that Web site or by calling
the Diamond hot line at (800) 711-6066.
</P>
<P>
   Diamond is currently performing in Australia and New Zealand. He
begins a West Coast tour July 31 in San Diego.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
