monumental 2-0 lead home to the Garden by winning their seventh
consecutive playoff game. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-THOMAS (Indianapolis) _ Kurt Thomas, the brawny
Knicks forward, is trying to assert himself against the Pacers. By
Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SPURS (San Antonio) _ Folo on the Spurs' come-from-behind
victory over Portland in Game 2. By Chris Broussard.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-INDIANS (New York) _ Yankees vs. Cleveland, 7:35 p.m.
By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-RAMIREZ-BAT (New York) _ Did Manny Ramirez use a corked bat
in hitting a first-inning home run to dead center field on Monday,
as the Yankees suspect? And what happened to that bat, since
Ramirez didn't use it for the remainder of the game? By Murray
Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-REDS (New York) _ Reds at Mets, 7:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-FRENCH-WOMEN (Paris) _ A Hall of Fame lineup advances to the
