<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By FRANK J. PRIAL    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Pommery Brut Champagne, nonvintage. About $24 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Anyone who has visited Les Crayeres, the Michelin three-star
restaurant and hotel in Reims, France, has seen the ornate
buildings of the house of Pommery, just across the street. Louise
Pommery, one of the famous Champagne widows, put the company on the
map in the mid-19th century. Her daughter built Les Crayeres as her
home. Some years ago, the house went through a rough period, and
the wine was not up to the mark. No longer: this is a top-quality
Champagne, full flavored with a long, dry finish. The price is more
than reasonable.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
