A8579 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-PEARL-GO-LADN     06-01 0240
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PEARL-GO-LADN </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IF YOU GO:
</P>
<P>
   GETTING THERE: From Waikiki or downtown Honolulu, follow the H-1
freeway west to the USS Arizona/Stadium exit, which is No. 15A.
Follow the signs to the memorial, which is directly off state route
99. The ticket booth for the Battleship Missouri Memorial is next
to the USS Arizona Memorial parking lot.
</P>
<P>
   COSTS: There is no charge to visit the USS Arizona Memorial.
Admission for the Battleship Missouri Memorial is $10 for adults,
$6 for children ages 4 to 12 (3 and under free). Guided tours are
an additional $4 per person. The Missouri Signature Tour, which
includes round-trip transportation from Waikiki hotels and access
to areas of the ship not open to the general public, costs $29 for
adults, $19 for children ages 4 to 12.
</P>
<P>
   HOURS: The USS Arizona Memorial is open seven days a week, 7
a.m. to 5 p.m.; closed Thanksgiving, Christmas and New Year's Day.
The first showing of the documentary film is at 7:45 a.m. in the
summer (8 a.m. the rest of the year). The last program of the day
begins at 3 p.m. The Battleship Missouri Memorial is open daily
from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   INFORMATION: The USS Arizona Memorial's information line is
(808) 422-0561. Web: www.ups.gov/usar. Information on the
Battleship Missouri Memorial is available at (877) 644-4896.
Visitors on Oahu can call 973-2494. Web: www.ussmissouri.com. &QL; 
