call in November 1995 while still manager of Fidelity Magellan, the
world's largest mutual fund: He bailed out of $10 billion worth of
technology stocks. Now Vinik, whose Vinik Asset Management LP
manages about $2.5 billion, has slashed his technology holdings
once again, according to federal securities filings. By Richard A.
Oppel Jr.
