hundreds of tons of anthrax bacteria to this remote island in the
heart of the inland Aral Sea. Russian soldiers buried the germs
and, Moscow hoped, a grave political threat. Today, Vozrozhdeniye
Island _ or Renaissance Island, as it translates from the Russian _
is the world's largest anthrax burial ground. But scientists who
have secretly traveled here have discovered that some of the
anthrax spores are still alive. By Judy Miller. (The report has
