MEXICO-BABY-SMUGGLING, 6-1 -- Martina Toscano Quiroz, center, with
her children, Sussena Enriquez, 11, left, and Aurelia, 12, in their
two- room shack near the Mexican border with Arizona. Last week, a
lawyer and two women in New York were arrested and charged with
running a cross-country baby-smuggling ring that the U.S.
government says sold Ms. Toscano's children, and at least 14
others, for up to $22,000 each to couples in New York, preying on
their desperation to have children. (Monica Almeida/New York Times
Photo) LITE
