<DOCNO> NYT19990601.0358 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 21:55 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9032 &Cx1f; taf-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-QUOTE-OF-THE-DAY-NYT     06-01 0077
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-QUOTE-OF-THE-DAY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE QUOTATION OF THE DAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-MEXICO-BABY-SMUGGLING-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I have had attorneys come here and offer me $100 for every
child I give to them for adoptions. I tell them my children are not
tomatoes for sale, and that I never want to see them on my property
again.''
</P>
<P>
   _EUNICIA SOTO, who runs an orphanage in Mexico.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
