<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the additional
story for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, June 2, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Veronica Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   TV-DIVERSITY (Undated) _ Apparently, the networks are waiting
for the next century before they embrace this idea of diversity in
casting. Still, you'd think that before the big splash next year _
surely there'll a big splash, no? _ they could have ended the 20th
century with just a tiny acknowledgment of cultural reality. But,
with only a few exceptions, the fall slate of programming unveiled
last month by the networks is so white bread that Wonder must have
an exclusive sponsorship deal. The publicity stills for the new
fall shows look as if they came from the White Supremacy Survival
Camp and Photo Studio.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
