<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THREE DISQUALIFIED FROM USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Three USC football players have been academically
disqualified from the university, effectively ending their athletic
careers.
</P>
<P>
   Junior free safety Darnell Lacy, senior wide receiver Quincy
Woods and freshman offensive lineman Robby Wood were dismissed
following the completion of USC's spring semester last month.
</P>
<P>
   Two other players _ sophomore linebacker Darryl Knight and
junior defensive end Shamsud-Din Abdul-Shaheed _ have been
suspended from USC's season opener against Hawaii for poor academic
performance.
</P>
<P>
   Lacy's departure is the biggest blow for the Trojans. He was
listed as a co-starter at free safety following spring drills with
junior Ife Ohalete.
</P>
<P>
   ``The emergence of Darnell Lacy ... Darnell Lacy and Ife are
going tooth-and-nail against each other and we can't make a
decision,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said following spring practice.
``They're going into (fall) camp as co-starters. This area I feel
has been a surprise to me.''
</P>
<P>
   Lacy has battled academic problems since he arrived at USC.
Hackett suspended him from last year's season opener against Purdue
for academics.
</P>
<P>
   Woods, who originally came to USC as a quarterback, redshirted
last season after undergoing knee surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Woods' departure leaves USC with just four upperclassmen on
scholarship at wide receiver. And two of those _ Stan Guyness and
Troy Garner _ have torn ligaments in their knees in the past seven
months.
</P>
</TEXT>
